    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-05-27T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-05-27T05:00:00-05:00" n="140"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/2003: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-05-27T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 27, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 27—6:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>666. If convenient I would appreciate your sending me by cable for my information
                    text of Japanese reply to the President’s message <pb facs="0272" n="170"
                        xml:id="pg_170"/> of May 16th and résumé of any conversations you may have
                    had with Viscount Ishii with respect to disarmament matters.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
